Talk with @yael_malka and you will be fascinated how much she is eager to explain and talk about her photography!

(please @yael_malka correct me if I'm wrong in any part :).)

7/7

Yes!

If this photo was done in pos-production with photoshop wouldn't be as magical as it is now. 

So method for me is one of the reasons I might buy a photo, since I value that part of the art as much as the end result. 

6/7

So not only the photo is aesthetically pleasing, the method used is super original and only a few photographers could achieve this flawless result. 

This brings me to a questions I ask several times - Does the method used to take a photo matter for its value? 

5/7 https://t.co/vryqOSR2Gs

@yael_malka Decided to make some stents to place on the front of the film and this way, preventing the light to get into certain areas. 

If not mistaken this a 1 photo from a total of 3 shots. 
you can see the stents here on this picture

4/7 https://t.co/PBdPg9zw08

On top of the great play of colour and subject,the composition is super original. That is what made me look at the photo originally. But this collection is a gift that keeps on giving

The most amazing aspect of this photo is the fact it isn't a collage and it's on filmü§Ø

3/7

First of all, the photo I'm talking about is https://t.co/DRJTyo0yHF
from @yael_malka
